docs.abstract: President Trump’s trade war is stirring uncertainty, weighing on manufacturing and disrupting increasingly delicate global economic growth.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s trade war is stirring uncertainty, weighing on manufacturing and disrupting increasingly delicate global economic growth.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump’s trade war is chilling business investment, confidence and trade flows across the world, a development that foreign leaders and business executives say is worsening a global economic slowdown that was already underway.

headline.main: Global Economic Growth Is Already Slowing. The U.S. Trade War Is Making It Worse.
headline.print_headline: Trump’s War Is Making A Slowdown Even Worse

docs.abstract: The skinny waterway, the gateway for a third of all crude oil by tanker, has become a security risk that could threaten the oil market.
docs.snippet: The skinny waterway, the gateway for a third of all crude oil by tanker, has become a security risk that could threaten the oil market.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Strait of Hormuz, sometimes described as the world’s most important oil choke point, is a gateway for almost a third of all crude oil and other petroleum products carried by tanker.

headline.main: How Tanker Attacks in the Strait of Hormuz Could Affect Oil Prices

docs.abstract: Meredith will continue to run the magazine and website, but Authentic Brands Group, a marketing company, will control the rights to images and the name itself.
docs.snippet: Meredith will continue to run the magazine and website, but Authentic Brands Group, a marketing company, will control the rights to images and the name itself.
docs.lead_paragraph: The intellectual property of Sports Illustrated, the magazine whose monumental covers and narrative voices have helped define American sports since its debut 65 years ago, has been sold for $110 million to Authentic Brands Group, in an unusual transaction that suggests the magazine’s most coveted asset is its brand.

headline.main: Sports Illustrated, the Brand, Is Sold for $110 Million
headline.print_headline: A Brand Is Sold For $110 Million: Sports Illustrated

headline.main: These Influencers Aren’t Flesh and Blood, Yet Millions Follow Them

docs.abstract: The digital pinboard company’s stock price tumbled in after-hours trading after its first earnings report as a public company.
docs.snippet: The digital pinboard company’s stock price tumbled in after-hours trading after its first earnings report as a public company.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Pinterest has avoided many of the woes of other newly public tech companies. But on Thursday, it stumbled.

headline.main: Pinterest Posts Narrower Loss, but Falls Short of Wall St. Estimates

docs.abstract: The company owned by the Reimann family of Germany may not be well known. But it is a major force in the food and beverage industries, among others.
docs.snippet: The company owned by the Reimann family of Germany may not be well known. But it is a major force in the food and beverage industries, among others.
docs.lead_paragraph: The average person probably hasn’t heard of JAB Holding. The same can’t be said for the vast empire of brands — a stable that includes Keurig coffee pods, Dr Pepper, Snapple, Einstein Bros. Bagels and Krispy Kreme doughnuts — it amassed in years of deal-making. Here’s how the conglomerate, whose controlling family is now grappling with its Nazi past, flourished.

headline.main: What Is JAB? Owner of Panera, Snapple and Krispy Kreme Faces Its Nazi Past

byline.original: By Michael J. de la Merced

docs.abstract: British lawmakers questioned a Huawei executive on Monday about American allegations that the company poses a risk to national security.
docs.snippet: British lawmakers questioned a Huawei executive on Monday about American allegations that the company poses a risk to national security.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — A Huawei executive defended the company’s security practices in the face of tough questioning from members of the British Parliament on Monday, as the Chinese technology giant seeks to contain an American-led effort to ban it around the world.

headline.main: Huawei Tells Parliament It’s No Security Threat, Aiming to Avoid a Ban
headline.print_headline: Huawei Tells British Parliament It’s No Threat to Security

docs.abstract: Team NBC is set, but the lineup of candidates is not: The Democratic Party has yet to say which 20 presidential contenders will take the stage June 26 and 27.
docs.snippet: Team NBC is set, but the lineup of candidates is not: The Democratic Party has yet to say which 20 presidential contenders will take the stage June 26 and 27.
docs.lead_paragraph: The first debate of the Democratic presidential primary will be moderated by the news anchors Savannah Guthrie, Lester Holt, Chuck Todd and José Díaz-Balart of Telemundo, along with the MSNBC commentator Rachel Maddow, NBC News said on Tuesday.

headline.main: Rachel Maddow, Chuck Todd and Lester Holt Are Among Moderators of First Democratic Debate
headline.print_headline: Team NBC Is Named  For 2 Days Of Debate

docs.abstract: Amazon Restaurants, which was available in nearly 200 American cities, will officially close on June 24. The company says it will focus on grocery delivery.
docs.snippet: Amazon Restaurants, which was available in nearly 200 American cities, will officially close on June 24. The company says it will focus on grocery delivery.
docs.lead_paragraph: With the online restaurant delivery market growing ever more competitive, Amazon is discontinuing the service it started four years ago as an alternative to popular apps like Grubhub and UberEats.

headline.main: Amazon to End Its Restaurant Delivery Service
headline.print_headline: In Competitive Field, Amazon Ends Delivery Of Restaurant Food
